SIMPLE: confessional
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Confessional
<hw>Con*fes"sion*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>confessional</ets>.]</ety> <def>The recess, seat, or inclosed
place, where a priest sits to hear confessions; often a small structure
furnished with a seat for the priest and with a window or aperture so
that the penitent who is outside may whisper into the priest's ear
without being seen by him or heard by others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confessional</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Confessional
<hw>Con*fes"sion*al</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to a confession
of faith.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Confessional equality</b></col>, <cd>equality before the
law of persons confessing different creeds.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confessionalism</ent>⟦br⟧
